option.value:
in order to make InstantiationState creation easier and clearer - created an InstantiationStateCreator - changed all classes creating InstantiaionState instances to use the creator
- small refactorigns -- changed step name that was the default name to one that made more since in StepsWithCustomState class -- layed out the GivWenZenCreatorTest slightly different (hopefull more readable)

MESSAGE.value: rearranging in the order they are currently used, just easier for the screencasts

- fixed path issue in intellij examples module - fixed path issue in intellij main module - rearranged methods in GivWenZenForSlim to put the interface methods at the top - changed the example pw validatino tests to include the scenario at the top of the tests instead of using the ScenarioLibrary - hid the script row in the setup - removed the password validation with a single step class (not very nice)
- updated to FitNesse edge to get fixes for hidden first row - fixed tests to use - instead # for hidden first row
- had a local set of test deleted but not from subversion, removed from subversion

- in order to make customization of GivWenZen easier -- added ability to create with custom step state - updated usages in tests and examples that use custom package and/or custom step state to use the creator -- fixed intellij project issues
- in order to make customization of GivWenZen easier -- added ability to create with custom instantiation strategies - updated usages in tests and examples that use custom instantiation strategies
- in order to make customization of GivWenZen easier -- fixed the ant file to include fest jars

- in order to allow for multiple custom state objects -- refactored the GivWenZenExecutor to allow for 0 or more custom step state objects -- refactored GWZForJUnit (not sure how it was working before). I think the next step will be just to get rid of it. -- changed tests to use multiple custom state objects

in order to make InstantiationState creation easier and clearer - created an InstantiationStateCreator - changed all classes creating InstantiaionState instances to use the creator
- small refactorigns -- changed step name that was the default name to one that made more since in StepsWithCustomState class -- layed out the GivWenZenCreatorTest slightly different (hopefull more readable)
